~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  Literate programming-style documentation using Vim
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~


   HI :)  Vocco uses Vim's :TOhtml feature to
          render groups of files as syntax
          highlighted HTML, using your
          everyday Vim settings.

          Make sure you have MacVim or gvim
          and a nice default color scheme
          installed for optimum roi.

   USAGE  vocco [options] [glob ..]

          The HTML files will be written to
          output_dir.

          Files matching any of the supplied
          globs will be processed.

          If no globs are given, vocco will
          use these:


 OPTIONS
        --out   OUTPUT_DIR

        --name  PROJECT_NAME

        --site  PROJECT_URL

        --vim   VIM_COMMAND
        
        The --vim option specifies which
        executable to use when rendering.


DEFAULTS

      [glob..]  '**/*.rb', 'README', 'LICENCE'

        --out   './docs'

        --name  Get from gemfile, or use
                current directory name.

        --site  Get from gemspec if available.

        --vim   macvim,gvim,vim


GREETS    Docco
           http://jashkenas.github.com/docco/
          Rocco
